  <summary date="2021-03-11T15:34:43Z" status="Introduced in House">Medical Debt Relief Act of 2021 

This bill modifies requirements related to the reporting of medical debt. Specifically, a consumer reporting agency is prohibited from adding medical debt information to a consumer credit report if the debt

 was fully paid or settled, or is less than a year old. Additionally, a debt collector must notify the consumer prior to reporting medical debt to a consumer reporting agency.</summary>
